From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Disable -threaded for ghc.exe on Windows to avoid builderMainLoop error

The bootstrap GHC on Windows triggers "builderMainLoop: invalid argument"
errors when linking ghc.exe with -threaded. This happens because GHC spawns
multiple processes during linking which fail on Azure CI Windows.

This patch disables the -threaded flag for the ghc executable on Windows
by checking windowsHost before using threadedBootstrapper.

diff --git a/hadrian/src/Settings/Packages.hs b/hadrian/src/Settings/Packages.hs
--- a/hadrian/src/Settings/Packages.hs
+++ b/hadrian/src/Settings/Packages.hs
@@ -5,6 +5,7 @@ import Flavour
 import Oracles.Setting
 import Oracles.Flag
 import Packages
+import Hadrian.Utilities (windowsHost)
 import Settings

 -- | Package-specific command-line arguments.
@@ -84,8 +85,10 @@ packageArgs = do
             , notM cross `cabalFlag` "terminfo"
             , ifM stage0
                   -- We build a threaded stage 1 if the bootstrapping compiler
-                  -- supports it.
-                  (threadedBootstrapper `cabalFlag` "threaded")
+                  -- supports it. Disabled on Windows to avoid builderMainLoop
+                  -- errors when the bootstrap GHC spawns processes during linking.
+                  ((if windowsHost then pure False else threadedBootstrapper)
+                    `cabalFlag` "threaded")

                   -- We build a threaded stage N, N>1 if the configuration calls
                   -- for it.
